## Spec corrections made live during Red-phase test-writing (not assumed, VERIFIED
## against the actual pre-existing src/commands/wallet.ts before writing tests)

REQ-FUND-001/007 originally claimed `deposit` resolves its target chain via "the
`--chain` flag if given, else the currently-active chain — same resolution status/
chain actions already use." Reading `src/commands/wallet.ts`'s ACTUAL `status`/
`deposit` action code (both call `getChain()` only, no `--chain` flag ever
referenced) proved this false. Corrected: `deposit` reads ONLY `getChain()` (the
persisted/session-active chain); a `--chain` flag has NO EFFECT on `deposit`
(REQ-FUND-007b, new). `.vcsdd/features/blockrun-cli-funding-dx/specs/{behavioral
-spec,verification-architecture}.md` updated accordingly; PROP-FUND-005's test
rewritten from "explicit --chain solana never mints" (which was testing a
resolution rule that doesn't exist) to "a --chain solana flag alongside an
ACTIVE-Base wallet has no effect — the mint still happens" (REQ-FUND-005/007b).

## Mock-plumbing bugs caught and fixed BEFORE reaching a stable RED (same class of
## issue blockrun-cli-agent-dx's Phase 2a already hit twice with shell/http.js)

- `mock.module("../../src/shell/qr.js", { namedExports: { openUrl: ... } })`
  initially provided ONLY `openUrl`, but `commands/wallet.ts` ALSO imports
  `generateQrPng`/`openQrInViewer` from that same module (for the pre-existing qr/
  setup actions) — a partial mock REPLACES the whole module, so this crashed the
  ENTIRE wallet.test.ts file with `SyntaxError: module does not provide an export`.
  Fixed by adding harmless stub implementations for both.
- Initial deposit test assertions assumed `parsed.address === "0xBASE"` (the mocked
  `ensureBaseWallet()` value) — but the EXISTING `deposit` action actually sources its
  address from `getWalletInfo()` (mocked separately as `"0xTEST"`), a DIFFERENT mock
  value in this test file (both route to the SAME real wallet in production; the
  mocks just happen to diverge). Since REQ-FUND-004 requires `deposit`'s pre-existing
  address-sourcing to stay UNCHANGED, the test assertions were corrected to
  `"0xTEST"`, not the implementation retargeted to `ensureBaseWallet()`.

